description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a motivated Band 4 Therapy Assistant to work within our friendly and supportive Occupational Therapy Orthopaedic Team. They will be working with patients that have had Orthopaedic surgery for a wide range of conditions, both completed electively and as a result of trauma. They will be a valued member of the team completing both assessments and interventions with patients to facilitate their safe discharge home from hospital and part of a wider multi disciplinary team. The role will include seeing patients both pre and post-operatively. They will also assist with the day to day running of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will need to have good communication and organisational skills and have had experience of working within the health care setting; they will need to have had experience of completing assessments and interventions with patients: experience of completing patient education would also be beneficial. Some autonomous working as well as the ability to work as an integrated member of the multi disciplinary team will be an integral part of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloisng date: 01/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
